<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1398,928,1066]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Cockerell also mentioned a male specimen collected in San José, 
<collectingCountry box="[955,1082,928,954]" name="Guatemala" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
on 
<date box="[1125,1357,928,954]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1946-12-22">December 22, 1946</date>
, by A. Pelén, probably Amador Pelén Cantoral (
<date box="[699,837,965,991]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1923" valueMax="2007">1923–2007</date>
), an former student and employee of the Escuela Agrícola Panamericana (
<bibRefCitation author="Pitty" box="[481,612,1002,1028]" firstAuthor="Pitty" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref21651" refString="Pitty A. 2008. Amado Pelen Cantoral, una vida dedicada al servicio de la Escuela Agricola Panamericana. Revista Ceiba 49: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2008">Pitty 2008</bibRefCitation>
). It is not clear whether this specimen belonged to the 
<typeStatus box="[1265,1316,1003,1029]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
series, and unfortunately, it was not found during this research.
</paragraph>
